beauty, family, care, and belonging-that are reaching a boiling point as the country struggles to deal with the same migration pressures that are triggering backlash all over Europe and North America. Tight Knit tells a fascinating story about the heterogeneity of contemporary capitalism that will interest social scientists, immigration experts, and anyone curious about how globalization is changing the most basic of human conditions-making a living and making a life.     aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aClothing tradexSocial aspectszItaly. 0aClothing workerszItalyzPratoxSocial conditions. 0aForeign workers, ChinesezItalyzPratoxSocial conditions. 0aGlobalizationxSocial aspectszItaly. 0aImmigrant familieszItalyzPratoxSocial conditions. 0aImmigrantszItalyxSocial conditions. 4aChinese migrants. 4aItaly. 4aeconomic anthropology. 4afamilies. 4afast fashion. 4aglobalization. 4ahealth and well-being. 4aimmigration. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226558103423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226558103.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles